				<div id="post-100" class="post-100 page type-page status-publish hentry">
											<h1 class="entry-title">Why I Do This</h1>
					
					<div class="entry-content">
						<p><a href="http://www.unmitigatedbadassery.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/MeRed.jpg" rel="lightbox[100]"><img class="wp-image-728 alignleft" title="Me." src="http://www.unmitigatedbadassery.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/MeRed.jpg" alt="" width="155" height="155" /></a>I started this site after years of being ridiculously unhealthy. I&#8217;m not an expert or an athlete by any means. In fact, I&#8217;m still considerably overweight but I&#8217;m on the right track. For me <a title="Iron and the Soul" href="http://www.unmitigatedbadassery.com/iron-and-the-soul/">motivation</a> comes in many forms. One of the most powerful forms is my drive to not let anyone down as well as my personal belief that we all have a responsibility to help one another in anyway we can. I have awesome readers so I feel compelled to produce great content. To produce great content I have to experience it and if I experience it then I can add another notch in my bed post of life and be a better me.</p>
<p><strong>That&#8217;s great but what do you get out of it?</strong></p>
<p>To be honest, I can&#8217;t offer any more than my experience and share the things I&#8217;m learning along the way. I have high hopes that someone somewhere will find something inspirational or otherwise useful, even one sentence, that I have written.</p>
<p><strong>This site would rock a lot more with your help.</strong></p>
<p>I&#8217;m asking you very nicely to submit some ideas or things you would like to see added here.</p>
<p>If so inclined, you can read my<a title="Iâ€™ve been there (Pt. I)" href="http://www.unmitigatedbadassery.com/ive-been-there-pt-i/"> whole story </a>about challenges that have molded me into the guy I am today as well as where the name <a title="Badassery: Origins" href="http://www.unmitigatedbadassery.com/badassery-origins/">Unmitigated Badassery </a>came from.</p>
																	</div><!-- .entry-content -->
